    • Method Detail

      • getTransactions

        public TransactionCursor getTransactions​(LogPosition position)
                                  throws IOException
        Description copied from interface: LogicalTransactionStore
        Acquires a cursor which will provide CommittedTransactionRepresentation instances for committed transactions, starting from the specified LogPosition. This is useful for placing a cursor at a position referred to by a CheckpointInfo. Transactions will be returned from the cursor in transaction-id-sequential order.
        Specified by:
        getTransactions in interface LogicalTransactionStore
        Parameters:
        position - LogPosition of the first transaction that the cursor will return.
        Returns:
        an TransactionCursor capable of returning CommittedTransactionRepresentation instances for committed transactions, starting from the specified position.
        Throws:
        NoSuchTransactionException - if the requested transaction hasn't been committed, or if the transaction has been committed, but information about it is no longer available for some reason.
        IOException - if there was an I/O related error looking for the start transaction.

      • getTransactionsInReverseOrder

        public TransactionCursor getTransactionsInReverseOrder​(LogPosition backToPosition)
        Description copied from interface: LogicalTransactionStore
        Acquires a cursor which will provide CommittedTransactionRepresentation instances for committed transactions, starting from the end of the whole transaction stream back to (and including) the transaction at LogPosition. Transactions will be returned in reverse order from the end of the transaction stream and backwards in descending order of transaction id.
        Specified by:
        getTransactionsInReverseOrder in interface LogicalTransactionStore
        Parameters:
        backToPosition - LogPosition of the lowest (last to be returned) transaction.
        Returns:
        an TransactionCursor capable of returning CommittedTransactionRepresentation instances for committed transactions in the given range in reverse order.

      • getTransactions

        public TransactionCursor getTransactions​(long transactionIdToStartFrom)
                                  throws IOException
        Description copied from interface: LogicalTransactionStore
        Acquires a cursor which will provide CommittedTransactionRepresentation instances for committed transactions, starting from the specified transactionIdToStartFrom. Transactions will be returned from the cursor in transaction-id-sequential order.
        Specified by:
        getTransactions in interface LogicalTransactionStore
        Parameters:
        transactionIdToStartFrom - id of the first transaction that the cursor will return.
        Returns:
        an TransactionCursor capable of returning CommittedTransactionRepresentation instances for committed transactions, starting from the specified transactionIdToStartFrom.
        Throws:
        NoSuchTransactionException - if the requested transaction hasn't been committed, or if the transaction has been committed, but information about it is no longer available for some reason.
        IOException - if there was an I/O related error looking for the start transaction.
